[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    438[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mEligibility filters as hard constraints.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Step 3's OpenSearch filter clause includes status, network_tier (from [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mPLAN_TIER_ELIGIBILITY[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m), language, gender, accepts_new_patients, and geographic radius. Out-of-network providers cannot reach the ranker. Pediatricians can't appear in adult searches once the canonical specialty filter applies. Closed panels can't appear for new-patient queries. The eligibility-vs-optimization boundary is enforced where the recipe says it should be (at the top of the stack, before scoring).[K
